Section 1:
1 L.D. 1611
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 LABOR
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1065, L.D. 1611, “An Act to Decrease
10 the Retirement Contributions Required for Teachers and State Employees”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §17154, sub-§6, ¶K is enacted to read:
14 K. Notwithstanding this section, beginning July 1, 2027, the additional employer
15 retirement costs that are applicable to the normal cost of retirement for a teacher
16 pursuant to section 17701-C must be paid by the State.
17 Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §17701-B, as amended by PL 2007, c. 491, §104, is further
18 amended to read:
19 §17701-B. Member contributions on and after July 1, 1993 until June 30, 2027
20 Notwithstanding sections 17701 and 17701‑A, on and after July 1, 1993 until June 30,
21 2027, all members shall contribute to the State Employee and Teacher Retirement Program
22 or have pick-up contributions made at a rate of 7.65% of earnable compensation except as
23 otherwise provided in this Part.
24 Sec. 3. 5 MRSA §17701-C is enacted to read:
25 §17701-C. Member contributions on and after July 1, 2027
26 1. Member contributions on and after July 1, 2027. Notwithstanding sections
27 17701, 17701-A and 17701-B, on and after July 1, 2027, except as otherwise provided in
28 this Part, all members shall contribute to the State Employee and Teacher Retirement
29 Program or have pick-up contributions made at a rate of earnable compensation as follows:
30 A. From July 1, 2027 until June 30, 2028, 7.4%;
31 B. From July 1, 2028 until June 30, 2029, 7.15%;
32 C. From July 1, 2029 until June 30, 2030, 6.9%;
33 D. From July 1, 2030 until June 30, 2031, 6.65%;
Page 1 - 132LR1215(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1065, L.D. 1611
1 E. From July 1, 2031 until June 30, 2032, 6.4%; and
2 F. On and after July 1, 2032, 6.2%.'
3 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
4 number to read consecutively.
5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill. The
77 amendment provides that, beginning on July 1, 2027, the percentage of contributions that
88 members of the Maine Public Employees Retirement System must contribute will gradually
99 reduce from the current rate of earnable compensation of 7.65% to 6.2% by July 1, 2032.
1100 The amendment also requires increased employer retirement costs applicable to the normal
1111 cost of retirement for teachers due to this change to be paid by the State.
1122 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1133 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1215(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
